      <section eId="sec_CHC-1514">
        <num>CHC 1514</num>
        <heading>1514. Â Petition for voluntary transfer</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1514__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A proceeding under this Chapter shall be commenced by written petition.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1514__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Except as otherwise provided in this Article, all persons or organizations lawfully exercising legal custody of the child shall join in the petition.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1514__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>If a legal custodian is unable or unwilling to join in the petition, the petition shall state with particularity the reasons therefor.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1514__subsec_D">
          <num>D.</num>
          <content>
            <p>If a guardian has been appointed, a petition for voluntary transfer may not be filed. To change a guardianship order a motion to modify the guardianship may be filed in accordance with Article 724.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=72982</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
